    slug: "hazrat-ibrahim-as-bahasit-walid",
    description: `Hazrat Ibrahim AS Bahasit Walid is an Urdu-language book that narrates the life story of Prophet Ibrahim (peace be upon him) through the lens of a child's curiosity and perspective. Written as part of the Bahasit Walid series, which translates to "Words of the Child," this book adopts a unique storytelling approach where a young reader poses questions about the life, trials, and unwavering faith of Prophet Ibrahim. The narrative structure is designed to engage children directly, making complex historical and religious events accessible to young minds. The book covers the major episodes from Prophet Ibrahim's life, including his early search for the true Creator while living among idol-worshipping people in Mesopotamia, his destruction of the idols, his miraculous survival after being thrown into the fire by his own community, his migration to Palestine and Egypt, and his unwavering trust in Allah during times of extreme hardship. The sacrifice of Prophet Ibrahim, which is commemorated every year during Eid ul-Adha, is presented in a manner that children can understand and connect with emotionally. The book emphasizes the themes of tawheed (monotheism), complete submission to the will of Allah, and the rewards that come with patience and steadfast faith. Each chapter introduces a new event from the life of Prophet Ibrahim and follows it with reflections that a child might naturally express, helping young readers internalize the moral and spiritual lessons embedded in these stories. The language used throughout the book is simple yet meaningful, suited for primary and middle school-aged children. Parents and teachers will find this book to be an excellent resource for bedtime storytelling, Islamic school curricula, and family reading sessions. The hardbound card cover ensures durability, making it suitable for repeated handling by children. By presenting the biography of one of the most revered prophets in Islam through this child-centered format, the book fosters a lifelong love for learning about the lives of the prophets and strengthens the foundation of Islamic faith in young readers from an early age.`,
    metaDescription: "Hazrat Ibrahim AS Bahasit Walid is an Urdu children's book narrating Prophet Ibrahim's life through a child's perspective. Ideal for young readers."
