    slug: "hazrat-ibrahim-as-ki-qurbani-ka-qissa",
    description: `Hazrat Ibrahim AS ki Qurbani ka Qissa is an Urdu-language book that retells the iconic story of the sacrifice of Prophet Ibrahim (peace be upon him) in a manner suitable for readers of all ages, with particular emphasis on making the narrative understandable and engaging for younger audiences. The book focuses specifically on the event of Qurbani, one of the most significant episodes in Islamic history, where Prophet Ibrahim saw in a dream that he was being commanded by Allah to sacrifice his beloved son Prophet Ismail. The narrative walks the reader through every stage of this profound event, beginning with the dream itself, Prophet Ibrahim's discussion with his son about what he had seen, and the remarkable response of young Prophet Ismail who willingly submitted to the command of Allah. The book describes the journey to Mina, the preparation for the sacrifice, and the divine intervention that replaced Prophet Ismail with a ram at the final moment. This event established the annual ritual of Eid ul-Adha, and the book connects this historical incident to the modern practice of animal sacrifice performed by Muslims around the world each year. Written in clear and flowing Urdu, the book uses descriptive language that brings the setting and emotions of the characters to life without departing from the authentic sources of Islamic narration. The author draws upon the Quran and authenticated hadith literature to ensure accuracy while maintaining a narrative style that holds the reader's attention. The book serves multiple purposes within a household or educational setting. For parents, it provides a structured way to explain the meaning and significance of Qurbani to their children during the days of Eid ul-Adha. For Islamic school teachers, it serves as supplementary reading material that enriches the curriculum on the lives of the prophets. The card cover binding makes it a sturdy and long-lasting addition to any home library. By focusing on this single but immensely important event from the life of Prophet Ibrahim, the book allows readers to fully absorb the lessons of submission, faith, and divine mercy that this story represents in Islamic tradition.`,
    metaDescription: "Read the complete story of Hazrat Ibrahim AS and the sacrifice of Qurbani in Urdu. A detailed narrative for all ages about this key Islamic event."
