    slug: "hidayat-al-qari-sharh-sahih-al-bukhari-10-volume-set-local",
    description: `Hidayat al-Qari Sharh Sahih al-Bukhari is an extensive 10-volume commentary on Sahih al-Bukhari, the most revered collection of hadith in Sunni Islam. This local edition presents a detailed explanatory text (sharh) that accompanies each hadith narrated by Imam Muhammad ibn Ismail al-Bukhari, providing readers with context, linguistic analysis, and scholarly insights that illuminate the meaning and significance of each narration. The title "Hidayat al-Qari" translates to "Guidance for the Reader," reflecting the fundamental purpose of this commentary, which is to make the sometimes complex and terse language of hadith accessible to contemporary readers who may not have advanced training in the classical Islamic sciences. Each volume of this set covers a specific section (kitab) of Sahih al-Bukhari, following the organizational structure established by Imam al-Bukhari himself. The commentary draws upon multiple classical sources, including the explanations provided by earlier scholars such as Ibn Hajar al-Asqalani in his famous Fath al-Bari, while also incorporating observations and clarifications that address the needs of modern readers. The explanatory notes cover a wide range of topics related to each hadith, including the meaning of uncommon Arabic words and phrases, the biographical information about the narrators in the chain (isnad), the circumstances under which each hadith was spoken (asbab al-wurud), the jurisprudential implications derived from each narration, and the connections between related hadith within the same chapter or across different chapters. This 10-volume local edition makes this substantial scholarly work more accessible in terms of both affordability and availability compared to imported editions. The binding of each volume is designed for durability, recognizing that this is a reference set that will be consulted frequently by scholars, students, and serious readers of hadith. Islamic seminaries (madaris), university libraries, research institutions, and individual scholars will find this set to be an invaluable addition to their collections. The text is printed in a clear and legible format with proper formatting of Arabic text, hadith references, and footnotes, making navigation through the extensive material straightforward and efficient.`,
