    slug: "hisn-ul-muslim-12x17",
    description: `Hisn ul Muslim, meaning "Fortress of the Muslim," is one of the most widely used and trusted compilations of daily supplications (dua) and remembrances (adhkar) in the Muslim world. This edition, measuring 12 by 17 centimetres, strikes a practical balance between portability and readability, making it an ideal size for regular use at home, in the mosque, or during travel. Originally compiled by Sa'id ibn Ali ibn Wahf al-Qahtani, Hisn ul Muslim has become the standard dua reference book recommended by scholars, teachers, and Islamic institutions globally due to its rigorous authentication process and its comprehensive coverage of every significant occasion in a Muslim's daily life. The book organizes supplications into clearly defined sections, beginning with the morning and evening adhkar that every Muslim is encouraged to recite daily for spiritual protection and blessings. Subsequent sections cover dua for Salah (prayer), including supplications recited during the various positions of prayer and after completing the prayer. The book includes dua for eating and drinking, supplications for entering and leaving the home, prayers for wearing new clothes, dua for using the washroom, and supplications for travelling by various means of transportation. Additional sections address specific needs such as dua for seeking forgiveness (istighfar), supplications for protection from the evil eye and envy, prayers for healing during illness, dua for times of anxiety and sorrow, and supplications for success in examinations and business dealings. Every dua in this compilation is accompanied by its reference to the authentic hadith sources, primarily from Sahih al-Bukhari, Sahih Muslim, and the four major Sunan collections, giving the reader confidence in the authenticity of each included prayer. The 12x17 centimetre format provides ample page size for the Arabic text to be printed clearly and legibly, while the book remains compact enough to fit comfortably on a bookshelf, in a desk drawer, or in a travel bag. This edition is particularly popular as a gift item for new Muslims, graduates, and anyone beginning their journey of incorporating regular dua into their daily routine.`,
    metaDescription: "Hisn ul Muslim (12x17) is a comprehensive daily dua collection with authenticated supplications for every occasion, in a practical medium-sized format."
