    slug: "historical-atlas-of-the-prophets-messengers",
    description: `The Historical Atlas of the Prophets and Messengers is a unique and visually rich reference book published by Darussalam that combines cartography, historical research, and Islamic scholarship to present the geographical and historical context of the lives of the prophets mentioned in the Quran. This atlas is the first of its kind in the English language to focus specifically on mapping the locations, journeys, and events associated with the prophets of Islam, making it an invaluable resource for anyone seeking to understand the historical and geographical dimensions of prophetic history. The book features detailed, full-colour maps that pinpoint the locations associated with each prophet, including the cities where they lived, the regions where they preached, the routes of their journeys and migrations, and the sites of major events described in the Quran and Islamic tradition. Each map is accompanied by explanatory text that provides historical context, identifies the modern-day countries and cities that correspond to the ancient locations, and explains the significance of each site in the story of the respective prophet. The atlas covers all the prophets mentioned by name in the Quran, starting with Prophet Adam (peace be upon him) and proceeding chronologically through Prophet Nuh, Prophet Hud, Prophet Salih, Prophet Ibrahim, Prophet Ismail, Prophet Ishaq, Prophet Yaqub, Prophet Yusuf, Prophet Musa, Prophet Dawud, Prophet Sulaiman, Prophet Isa, and finally Prophet Muhammad (peace be upon them all). For each prophet, the book provides not only maps but also relevant historical information about the civilizations and cultures in which they lived, the challenges they faced, and the communities they were sent to guide. The cartographic work in this atlas is based on extensive research using both Islamic historical sources and modern archaeological and geographical data, ensuring that the maps are as accurate as possible given the limitations of historical geography. The visual presentation makes complex historical information immediately accessible and engaging, allowing readers to literally see the sweep of prophetic history across time and space. This atlas is an excellent educational resource for Islamic schools, a valuable reference for researchers and students of Islamic history, and a fascinating read for any Muslim interested in deepening their understanding of the lives of the prophets and the lands in which they lived and preached.`,
    metaDescription: "The Historical Atlas of the Prophets and Messengers features full-colour maps and scholarly text tracing the lives and journeys of Quranic prophets."
